<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,225,251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="106">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niu &amp; Ascher &amp; Griswold &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Wu" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[325,580,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Bathanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[325,580,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="106">Bathanthidium bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<emphasis box="[785,960,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wu" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[785,956,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Bathanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barkamense">B. barkamense</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
They share the distinctive red tegulae and red markings on the legs, and both have a thin paraocular marking, the marking of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wu" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[1082,1249,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Bathanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barkamense">
<emphasis box="[1082,1249,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="106">B. barkamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
extending along the inner margin nearly to the top of the eye, but the marking of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niu &amp; Ascher &amp; Griswold &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Wu" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[871,983,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Bathanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[871,983,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="106">B. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only extending to the middle of the eye.
</paragraph>
